name: r-rly
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.7.4" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rly
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/rly_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/rly/rly_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 1f59fb906bacf1cae22fe54dd340137063229c8dbcb64aa1a85006fd02bb9910

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-futile.logger
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-r6
    - r-futile.logger

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('rly')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('rly')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/systemincloud/rly
  license: MIT
  summary: R implementation of the common parsing tools 'lex' and 'yacc'.
  license_family: MIT

  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE
extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
